                    "description": "Supervisors: Prof. dr. Lydia Krabbendam, Dr Martin Gevonden and Dr Georgia Eleftheriouand\n\nDuties:\nAs a researcher in the ALIVE project (https://www.alive4mentalhealth.org), my duties are divided into two work packages: 1) Developing and validating user-friendly and low-cost psychophysiological instruments for non-laboratory settings data collection. To achieve this goal, I am currently validating low-cost, versatile wearable heart rate sensors that transfer data via Bluetooth to a host device. Additionally, I am developing an open-source Python module to facilitate future validation studies, 2) Developing an adapted, cost-effective, and user-friendly self-regulatory and psychophysiological-based intervention.",
