                    "company": "Vrije Universiteit Amsterdam (VU Amsterdam)",
                    "description": "Supervisor: prof. dr. Lydia Krabbendam\n\nAbstract: \nProsocial risk-taking refers to the intersection of prosociality and risk-taking. In this study, we aimed to investigate what happens when teenagers are encouraged to take unknown risks to help their best friends. To achieve this, we used an adapted version of the well-known Balloon Analogue Risk Task. Our goal was to examine whether risk-taking could have an adaptive and positive side, namely, helping others. Through a within-subject design, we manipulated the conditions to link adolescents' prosocial behavior to a monetary risk to themselves. However, contrary to our initial hypothesis, we found that adolescents preferred to be less prosocial when there was a risk to themselves as a result of helping their friends.",
